    {
      "id": "9d8c0806-e3cd-4296-a95e-969fd7a8c53d",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "There is a problem with current classifiers of performance as they often are done in a course or a small subset of courses at the end of the course. Moreover, binary classification seems to be the preferred task. Thses limitations hinder the ability to provide meaningful feedback and student support. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "9d8c0806-e3cd-4296-a95e-969fd7a8c53d",
        "parent": {
